any recipe for black and white cookies a black and white cookie is a dessert covered on one half with vanilla frosting and on the other half by dark chocolate frosting widely known as the black and white cookie in some areas mainly boston and upstate new york the cookie is known as a half moon born in utica ny to the hemstroughts baking company the popularity of the half moon has since spread widely the cookie is technically not a cookie but a frosted circular drop cake it is more cake like in texture as compared to a crunchier cookie black and white cookies these dramatic cakelike cookies are a new york city favorite and we think they deserve a wider audience active time min start to finish min makes about cookies for cookies cups all purpose flour teaspoon baking soda teaspoon salt cup well shaken buttermilk teaspoon vanilla cup tablespoons unsalted butter softened cup granulated sugar large egg for icings cups confectioners sugar tablespoon light corn syrup teaspoons fresh lemon juice teaspoon vanilla to tablespoons water cup unsweetened dutch process cocoa powder preparation make cookies preheat oven to f whisk together flour baking soda and salt in a bowl stir together buttermilk and vanilla in a cup beat together butter and sugar in a large bowl with an electric mixer until pale and fluffy about minutes then add egg beating until combined well mix in flour mixture and buttermilk mixture alternately in batches at low speed scraping down side of bowl occasionally beginning and ending with flour mixture mix until smooth spoon cups of batter about inches apart onto a buttered large baking sheet bake in middle of oven until tops are puffed and pale golden and cookies spring back when touched to minutes transfer with a metal spatula to a rack and chill to cool quickly about minutes make icings while cookies chill stir together confectioners sugar corn syrup lemon juice vanilla and tablespoon water in a small bowl until smooth transfer half of icing to another bowl and stir in cocoa adding more water teaspoon at a time to thin to same consistency as white icing ice cookies turn cookies flat sides up then spread white icing over half of each and chocolate over other half cooks'note if you can stand the wait cookies taste better if cooled without being chilled Flour Pizza Vinegar Rice pudding Idli Rum Chili con carne Haggis Cuisine of the Southern United States Cold Stone Creamery Bengali cuisine Dairy Chocolate Salty Balls Barbecue Cookware and bakeware Cocoa Bacon Cuisine of the Philippines Soft drink Halva Cooking weights and measures Oreo Cuisine of Brazil Cuisine of Singapore Souffl__ Milkshake Baked Alaska Sugar beet Cheesecake French fries Muffin Tortilla Dim sum Confectionery Gatorade Cuisine of Malaysia Plastic Ramen Martini cocktail Maple syrup Baklava In-N-Out Burger Brewery Biscuit Horehound Girl Scout cookies Pop-Tarts Hot dog Korean cuisine French toast American Chinese cuisine Twix Peruvian cuisine Cantonese cuisine Cha chaan teng Welding Russian cuisine Puff pastry Casting Baking powder Potato Vanilla Yoghurt Food preservation Doughnut Sushi Mango Mai Tai Carbon dioxide Red velvet cake Bearnaise sauce Soap bubble Baking 